HTTP Parameter Pollution (HPP) is a technique used to bypass input validation and WAF (Web Application Firewall) rules by sending multiple instances of the same HTTP parameter in a single request. This technique can be used to manipulate the application's behavior by overriding the expected values of the parameters.

Here's an example of how you can use HTTP Parameter Pollution to bypass input validation and WAF rules in a simple PHP application:

Assume we have a PHP application with the following code:

```php
<?php
$url = "http://example.com/index.php?name=John&age=25";

if (isset($_GET['name']) && isset($_GET['age'])) {
    $name = $_GET['name'];
    $age = $_GET['age'];

    // Perform some validation on the name and age
    if (strlen($name) > 10 || is_numeric($age) !== true) {
        echo "Invalid input";
        exit;
    }

    // Perform some action with the name and age
    echo "Hello, $name. You are $age years old.";
}
?>
```

To bypass the input validation and WAF rules using HTTP Parameter Pollution, we can send multiple instances of the same parameters in the URL:

```
http://example.com/index.php?name=John&name=John&name=John&age=25&name=John&age=26&name=John&age=27&name=John&age=28
```

In this example, we have sent 5 instances of the 'name' parameter and 4 instances of the 'age' parameter. This will bypass the input validation as the PHP script will now have 6 different values for the 'name' parameter and 5 different values for the 'age' parameter.

The PHP script will still perform the validation on each instance of the parameters, but since there are multiple instances, it will still output the expected result even if the validation fails for some of the instances.

To bypass WAF rules, you can also use other techniques like URL encoding, query string manipulation, and parameter naming conventions to trick the WAF into thinking that the requests are different. For example, you can use URL encoding to encode the parameters as `%60name%60` and `%60age%60` to bypass WAF rules that look for specific parameter names.

